<p>Adding a change driver</p><p>Change drivers can be used to track bug fixes, feature
	 modifications, or other non-feature based changes. 
  </p> 
	  
		<p>Add change drivers and their information to CORDAP, so that you can
		  link them to work packages. By adding the information and linking to work
		  packages, the information is readily available to the content developers when
		  they begin work. 
		</p> 
	  
	  
		 
		   In 
			 My Products, expand the desired product. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click the desired release. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Change Drivers. 
		   
		  The list of change drivers included in the selected release
			 appears. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Create a new change driver. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Enter the details for the change driver. 
		   
		   
			 <p> 
			 <table> 
				 
					  
						 
						  Fields 
						   
						 
						 
						  Description 
						   
						 
					  
				   
					  
						 
						  Name 
						   
						 
						 
						  Enter a name to identify the change driver. 
						   
						 
					  
					  
						 
						  Description 
						   
						 
						 
						  Enter a description for the change driver. 
						   
						 
					  
					  
						 
						  Type 
						   
						 
						 
						  Identify if it is a change request or a feature
							 modification. 
						   
						 
					  
					  
						 
						  Feature 
						   
						 
						 
						  Selecting a feature links the change driver to that
							 feature. 
						   
						 
					  
				   
				 
			  
			 </table> 
		  </p> 
		  Click 
			 Save. 
		   
		 
	 